Seller's reply
Friend,it is because the Flash memory vendors are using decimal arithmetic: 1MB = 1000KB, 1G = 1000MB calculated, while the operating system using binary arithmetic: 1MB = 1024KB, 1GB = 1024MB and system will occupy a few space, then the available space will be a little bit less than manufacturers signed.
So there are some differences between display capacity and nominal capacity of flash memory products. Friend, you can google it .So the capacity of 16GB is 14~15GB,the card we sell is original.

Making a purchase March 12, 2015 (payment).
I get the goods May 7, 2015.
Not the fastest service, but is the slowest.
Further verification H2testW showed that:
Write Speed:
SD Card 1 - 8.26 Mbyte / s
SD Card 2 - 8.32 Mbyte / s
Reading speed on both SD cards 18.1 Mbyte / sec
It is obvious that no class 10
The capacity of both SD cards - 15 260 Mbyte. This is not 16GB.
Opening of the dispute did not solve as needed video evidence. And it does not upload to the server. If you are not ready for a fair deal, you can take these memory card.
The seller is not honest. With him I will no more have anything to do.

Dear friend, 15260MB=14.9GB, real capacity 16GB card is about 14.8GB-15.3GB, it is same of all brands including Sandisk and Samsung. Please google Micro SD card capacity and you will understand.
About speed, you can easily get 10MB+ with quality card reader or another computer, card speed is greatly affected by devices, you can see this information in Sandisk official website or other official website
Please read my item detail before leaving feedback, we are confident with our card quality.
Sorry about slow shipping, we also hope it will be faster.
